<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li><strong>About 4% of adults have more than 1 nightmare per week.</strong></li><li><strong>Imagery rehearsal therapy is a common treatment for nightmare disorder.</strong></li><li><strong>Targeted memory reactivation may enhance the effectiveness of imagery rehearsal therapy.</strong></li></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>“It was only a dream.”</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>It’s a common enough expression to be a cliché, but to those living with&nbsp;<a href="https://psychcentral.com/disorders/nightmare-disorder-symptoms" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">nightmare disorder</a>, the phrase brings little comfort.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Nightmare disorder is characterized by frequent nightmares that cause distress or impair your ability to function during everyday activities such as work or social situations.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>And even if you don’t have this disorder, you’re likely familiar with the occasional bad dream. A&nbsp;<a href="https://healthline.com/health/nightmares">nightmare</a>&nbsp;might cause you to wake up and they often leave you with a lasting feeling of fear or stress.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/sleep/imagery-rehearsal-therapy">Imagery rehearsal therapy (IRT)</a>&nbsp;is one commonly used treatment method for nightmare disorder.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Researchers in Switzerland recently published a&nbsp;<a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.cub.2022.09.032" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">study</a>&nbsp;in the journal&nbsp;<em>Current Biology</em>&nbsp;in which they combined IRT with targeted memory reactivation (TMR). The results might have you sleeping easier.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Let’s take a look at what they found and how you might be able to put those bad dreams to bed.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:embed {"url":"https://inline.healthline.com/r/ssr/628ff44a-cf14-4ba0-a759-9d66a738b95e?utm_campaign=hl-betterhelp-social-proof-mh-driver\u0026utm_medium=embed\u0026selector=%23m61dc9f0a-7e06-4cd0-9658-4a0ef11da6campd_firstQuarter_c2c7c76d-2250-4555-8e52-9488ce7e2b09+%3E+div+%3E+div\u0026csid=0dfcd49a-c551-4500-970d-729c344e0f33\u0026caid=fbcdc27f-5098-47f6-8442-ce24a7e8cf61\u0026ciid=8786a50b-6f32-4431-b5c7-6c01ea715ea9\u0026tenant=wk_1Tqf7EYzOKyxm4Gvq042rU0Uky0\u0026srckey=src_1Tqf7BF96WTbG5QbUndHWIgKoFo\u0026cxsid=37142fa2-dcf2-4846-9d62-eb11d2840cfb\u0026imre=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuaGVhbHRobGluZS5jb20vaGVhbHRoLW5ld3MvbmlnaHRtYXJlcy1yZXNlYXJjaGVycy1zYXktcGxlYXNhbnQtc291bmRzLWFuZC1vdGhlci10aGVyYXBpZXMtY2FuLXJlZHVjZS10aGVt\u0026_mfuuid_=790c1e29-f953-4c21-a4e8-18bc2bb6e84e\u0026width=750\u0026subId=betterhelp_hl_mid_mentalhealth_socialproofinline_37711"} -->
